---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'May 15, 2026';
---

<Layout title="Accessibility Statement | Dr. Alan S. Lee, DDS" description="Our commitment to accessibility and WCAG 2.1 AA compliance. Dr. Alan S. Lee, DDS ensures all patients can access our dental services.">
  <div class="content-section">
    <h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: {lastUpdated}</em></p>
    
    <h2>Our Commitment to Accessibility</h2>
    <p>Dr. Alan S. Lee, DDS is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. We continually improve the user experience for everyone and apply relevant accessibility standards to ensure our website is accessible to all patients and visitors.</p>
    
    <h2>Conformance Status</h2>
    <p>The <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1</a> defines requirements for designers and developers to improve accessibility for people with disabilities. It defines three levels of conformance: Level A, Level AA, and Level AAA. Our website aims to conform to <strong>WCAG 2.1 Level AA</strong>.</p>
    
    <h2>Measures We Take</h2>
    <p>We take the following measures to ensure accessibility of our website:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Include accessibility as part of our mission and values</li>
      <li>Integrate accessibility into our procurement practices</li>
      <li>Assign clear accessibility targets and responsibilities</li>
      <li>Employ formal accessibility quality assurance methods</li>
      <li>Ensure all images have meaningful alt text</li>
      <li>Provide keyboard navigation throughout the site</li>
      <li>Maintain proper heading hierarchy for screen readers</li>
      <li>Ensure sufficient color contrast ratios (minimum 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)</li>
      <li>Make all interactive elements accessible with assistive technologies</li>
      <li>Provide skip navigation links</li>
      <li>Use ARIA landmarks and labels where appropriate</li>
      <li>Support reduced motion preferences</li>
      <li>Ensure forms have proper labels and error messages</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Compatibility With Browsers and Assistive Technology</h2>
    <p>Our website is designed to be compatible with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge — last 2 versions)</li>
      <li>Screen readers (JAWS, NVDA, VoiceOver, TalkBack)</li>
      <li>Voice recognition software</li>
      <li>Keyboard-only navigation</li>
      <li>Mobile devices with accessibility features enabled</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Technical Specifications</h2>
    <p>Accessibility of this website relies on the following technologies:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>HTML5 semantic markup</li>
      <li>ARIA (Accessible Rich Internet Applications) attributes</li>
      <li>CSS for visual presentation and responsive design</li>
      <li>JavaScript for enhanced interactivity (all core content accessible without JS)</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Known Accessibility Limitations</h2>
    <p>Despite our best efforts, some limitations may exist:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Third-party embedded forms (JotForm) may have their own accessibility features outside our direct control. We select HIPAA-compliant form providers that prioritize accessibility.</li>
      <li>Some historical PDF documents in our forms library may not be fully accessible. We are working to provide accessible alternatives upon request.</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Feedback</h2>
    <p>We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of our website. If you encounter accessibility barriers, please contact us:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:+12092392990">(209) 239-2990</a></li>
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info@dralanlee.com">info@dralanlee.com</a></li>
      <li><strong>In Person:</strong> 715 N Main St, Manteca, CA 95336</li>
      <li><strong>Mail:</strong> Dr. Alan S. Lee, DDS, 715 N Main St, Manteca, CA 95336</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We try to respond to feedback within <strong>2 business days</strong> and to propose a solution within <strong>10 business days</strong>.</p>
    
    <h2>Disability Accommodations in Our Office</h2>
    <p>In addition to our digital accessibility efforts, our physical office is accessible:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Wheelchair accessible entrance and treatment areas</li>
      <li>Accessible restroom facilities</li>
      <li>Assistance available for patients with mobility challenges</li>
      <li>Large-print and translated materials available upon request</li>
      <li>Sign language interpreter services can be arranged with advance notice</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Formal Grievances</h2>
    <p>If you believe that our website does not comply with accessibility standards, you may file a grievance by contacting our office. We will investigate and respond within 15 business days.</p>
    
    <h2>Standards Referenced</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/" rel="noopener noreferrer">WCAG 2.1 Level AA</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.section508.gov/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Section 508 of the Rehabilitation Act</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.ada.gov/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA)</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.hhs.gov/civil-rights/for-individuals/disability/index.html" rel="noopener noreferrer">HHS Office for Civil Rights</a></li>
    </ul>
    
    <p><a href="/" class="btn-primary">Return to Home Page</a></p>
  </div>
</Layout>